{
  "name": "Wall of Force",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/magic/water/barrier-ice-wall-snow.webp",
  "system": {
    "itemKey": "",
    "description": "<p><span class=\"cf0\">You create a 2 Space tall, 4 Space long Wall within range. Make a DC 15 Spell Check.</span></p><ul><li><p><span class=\"cf0\"><strong>Failure:</strong> The Wall has 2 HP.</span></p></li><li><p><span class=\"cf0\"><strong>Success:</strong> The Wall has 3 HP.</span></p></li><li><p><span class=\"cf0\"><strong>Success (Each 5):</strong> +1 HP.</span></p></li></ul><p><span class=\"cf0\">Creatures in the area are pushed to the nearest unoccupied Space of their choice. Objects in the area that are not held or carried are moved to either side of the Wall (your choice for each object).</span></p><p><span class=\"cf0\"><strong>Forcefield:</strong> The Wall is translucent and acts as a solid surface, blocking movement but not sound or light. The Wall has Resistance (2) to all damage and a PD and AD equal to your Save DC.</span></p><p></p><p><em><strong>System Tip:</strong> Use @UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.summons.Actor.RDNyBJo1hpRDQg2o]{Wall of Force Helper} companion to represent that Wall's stats. Drop actor on the map and enable </em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Activate</span></strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Wall of Force</span></strong></em></span><em> feature. Still use Measurement Template to represent the Wall itself.</em></p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spell Enhancements</span></strong></span></p><p><strong>Range: (1 AP, Repeatable) </strong>The range of the Spell increases by 5 Spaces. You can use this Enhancement a maximum of two times.</p><p><strong>Area: (1 MP, Repeatable)</strong> The length of the Wall increases by 6 Spaces or the height of the Wall increases by 2 Spaces.</p><p><strong>Durable: (1 MP, Repeatable)</strong> The Resistance increases by 1 or the Forcefield has <strong>+2 HP</strong>.</p><p><strong>One-way Mirror: (1 MP) </strong>Choose one face of the Wall to stay translucent. Creatures on that side see through it normally, while creatures on the other side perceive it as a reflection.</p>",
